==========+++++++   File Permissions   ==========+++++++

Each file has three permission levels: owner, group, others.

Example output:

ls -l

-rwxr-xr-- 1 emmanuel devops 1024 Oct 8 18:20 script.sh

Symbol	Meaning
r	Read
w	Write
x	Execute

Change permissions:

chmod 755 script.sh

==========+++++++  Real-World DevOps Example ‚Äì Securing Scripts  ==========+++++++

When deploying critical scripts:

chmod 700 deploy_prod.sh


Only the owner (e.g., DevOps lead) can execute it ‚Äî ensuring security in production.

